Contact hours: Anytime, although keep in mind we are on the West Coast.

We can buy *any* amount of BTC - because of the current regulatory environment and since we are an actual legitimate Bitcoin business, for orders or multiple orders totalling $3000 or above, we require photo ID matching the addressee.

You can email us directly at cashforbtc@gmail.com.

Experienced - We have sent several Expresspost cash shipments to different clients and have had no problems. Cash will be sent to your specified address through Expresspost with tracking number. Package inside the Expresspost envelope will be professionally packed.

Fast Response - Get your cash within a few days (depending on Expresspost).

Trusted, Personalized Service - Pro Trader badge awarded by LocalBitcoins. For trust and confidence, please note our 100% positive feedback of over 100+ trades here:
https://localbitcoins.com/accounts/profile/cashforbtc/feedback/
We are also available for escrow services for a small fee.

Unless you have a feedback rating higher than us, coins must be sent to us first. We will also pay a 0.5% premium for coins sent directly to our receiving address.

Please send your:
1) Full name and address including postal code.
2) Amount in CAD$ you would like to sell.
3) Specify if you'd like the 0.5% extra by sending BTC directly to our receiving address.
4) Photo ID with address or photo ID without address and utility bill/other ID with address if the transaction(s) total $3000 or above. Address on documentation should match the mailing address.

To help us out, please choose a round figure for the amount of cash you'd like to receive (i.e. $5000). We do not send denominations lower than $50 so the amount will be rounded down to the nearest $50.

Open 7 days per week and late! Pro Trader badge awarded by LocalBitcoins. For trust and confidence, please note our 100% positive feedback of over 100+ trades here.

Contact hours: Anytime, although keep in mind we are on the West Coast. If you're on the East Coast then that means we are open later for you! (Generally until 8pm EST is when the banks close here.) You can email us directly at cashforbtc@gmail.com.

Cash will be deposited at your specified bank (CIBC, TD, RBC, BMO, Scotia) or Greater Vancouver-area credit union account (such as Vancity or Coast Capital).

We do not take trades with LocalBitcoins profiles < 90% feedback score. If your LocalBitcoins profile has less than 5 confirmed trades or at least 1 negative feedback then to prevent flakes you will need to send/release Bitcoins first. We will pay 0.5% more cash if you send bitcoins direct to our receiving address and you send first (LocalBitcoins takes 1%).

Please send us:
1) Full name on the account. No third party deposits are allowed.
2) Your bank.
3) Your transit number (5 digits).
4) Your account number.
5) Your phone number for verification and just in case we need to contact you if there are issues with your account information at the bank.
6) Let us know if you want to send direct to our address (for a 0.5% extra premium).

To help us out, please choose a round figure for the amount of cash you'd like to receive (i.e. $2500) vs. a specific figure of BTC which will result in an odd amount. Otherwise we will just round down to the nearest $50.

The maximum cash deposit per client per day is $2900. For transactions $3000 and above we can either do a wire (for a $40 fee), or we can deposit a bank draft ($10 fee) into your account.

We can buy *any* amount of BTC - since we are an actual legitimate Bitcoin business, for orders totalling $3000 or above, we require a one-time photo ID scan/picture sent to us.

Funds are available instantly after the deposit is made, as it's cash. For proof, you will see the deposit as available funds in your online banking and we can send you a photo of the physical deposit receipt.

We are also available for escrow services with a small fee.

We make two trips to the banks per day, once in the morning after 11am and before 3pm. Once again in the evening before the banks close.
